  "detailedRequirements": "In Topcoder Connect v2, we are using Discourse as underlying implemebation for messaging. &nbsp;Whenever a new post is created, Discourse automatically sends out an email notification to the users involved in that discussion. This email notification contains a link to Discourse, but what we want to do is to include a link to the Connect project instead.<br />\n<br />\nSo, assume there is a URL in connect that can redirect the user to the project based on the topic id, something like:<br />\n<br />\n{connect url}/messages/:topicId<br />\n<br />\nWe want to include this URL in the email that Discourse sends out.<br />\n<br />\nIn Discourse, under Settings -&gt; Customize -&gt; Email Templates, you can change all email templates that used to create those emails. This particular case we are talking about the email template called &quot;User Posted Pm&quot;, which is sent whenever a post happens in a private message topic.<br />\n<br />\nI have updated this template to look like this:<br />\n<br />\n&lt;body&gt;<br />\n&lt;p&gt;This is the text I want!!&lt;/p&gt;<br />\n<br />\n&lt;p&gt;[View Message](https://connect-v2.topcoder-dev.com/projects/bypostid/%{post_id})&lt;/p&gt;<br />\n&lt;/body&gt;<br />\n<br />\nAnd it kind of worked, the problem is that the email sent out from discourse has 2 versions, a html and a text version. This change in the template updated the text version of the email, but email clients like gmail seem to always display the html version of the email by default. in forum, you can find the example code of the message that is received in Gmail. Note that the first version of the message, which is text, has my change, the second version of the message, which is html, doesn&#39;t.<br />\n<br />\nThe only option that I think we have is to make a change to the Discourse code. but this will be the last consideration.<br />\n<br />\nSo, for this challenge we&#39;d like to figure out the following questions with your reach.<br />\n<br />\n1- Is it possible to configure Discourse to send the text version of the emails only?<br />\n2- Is it possible to change the html version of the message without making code changes?<br />\n3- Is it possible to add something to the message to force email clients to display the text version of the message instead of the html version of the message?<br />\n4- If code changes are really the only option, please provide the changes that need to be made to update the message template, and the steps to deploy it to the docker version of Discourse.&nbsp;<br />\n5- Any other options?<br />\n&nbsp;",
